    text: "Some other schools have a liking for extra-long swords. From the point of view of my strategy these must be seen as weak schools. This is because they do not appreciate the principle of cutting the enemy by any means. Their preference is for the extra-long sword and, relying on the virtue of its length, they think to defeat the enemy from a distance.",
    reflect: "Musashi despised the strategy of keeping distance — of winning without fully engaging. It was cowardice dressed as technique. Where in your life are you using the 'long sword' — trying to win from a safe distance rather than fully engaging?",
